GIT AND GITHUB TUTORIAL-

What is GIT(VCS- Version Control System)
	Distributed Version Control 
	Coordinates work between multiple developers
	Who made what changes and when
	Revert back at any time
	Local and remote repos
	
-- Stores files.

	keeps track of code history
	takes snapshots of your files
	you decide when to take a snapshot by making a commit
	you can visit any snapshot at any time
	you can stage files before committing
	
--Basic Commands
	$git init ## initialize Local Git repository
	$git add<file> ## Add files to index
	$git status ## check status of working tree
	$git commit ## commit changes in index
	
	--Remote repository commands
	(git hub or bitbucket)
	$git push - Pus the local repository to remote repository
	 have to add creds pwds or SSH keys 
	 
	 $git pull-if you want to pull the latest changes from remote repository 
	 if someone made the latest changes so you can use pull
	 
	 $git clone - will copy the remote repo to your local folder
	 
--Installing GIT
	Linux(Debian) - $ sudo apt-get install git
	linux(Fedora) - $ sudo yum install git
	Mac - http://git-scm.com/download/mac
	windows- http://git-scm.com/download/win
	

after installing git. gitbash window will open up. 
	gitbash first commands-  git --version 
	to check the version of the git

__ creating files from GIT
touch index.html ## will create a hmtl file names index in the folder
touch app.js ## will create a js file in the folder named app

before you start to work with git you want to enter your name and email address to git-
git config --global user.name 'Anshul Bakode'
git config --global user.email 'anshulbakode@gmail.com'

git add index.html ## to add index.html to git	
git rm --cached index.html ## to remove file from git staging area

git add *.html ## will add any html file present in the folder

to add every file in the git 
git add .


	
